I don’t have parents, I don’t really have blood family, and I don’t have a lot of friends. It was my choice, but it was a hard one to make and it definitely isn’t comfortable. I’m grateful to the few that have been patient with me. Healing doesn’t feel good.

When you don’t expect to be around long, you don’t find yourself making many solid plans. I was stuck in this cycle of surviving and burning out until I cut people out of my life who didn’t benefit me. Life isn’t 100% better, it probably never will be, and that’s okay.

There were many moments over the last few years where I really didn’t think I would last more than a few months or a year. That shit gets really hard and makes it impossible to be “productive” in any way

I’m really hard on myself about not being consistent, but I need to accept that I’m autistic AND I have ADHD with severe executive functioning issues. It’s okay to not be okay sometimes, or a lot of the time, or always.
